From: Azuki Miho Sub: Mashiro I read Hirameki!
It will definitely be a big hit with the kids!
You are always saying, No one will ever take an abrasive woman like you as a bride.
If a guy like that exists, I would like to meet him.
He wants to be a manga author, huh?
And he is got a new one starting in February.
Your friend was a manga author, was not he?
Do not bring that up now.
He literally put his life on the line to draw manga, and ended up dying because of it.
Was that friend of yours Kawaguchi Tarou, by any chance?
Shujin's probably being told something like
I will not hand my daughter over to a manga author with such an unstable future by now.
So you are working with his nephew.
It is like fate, is not it?
Can you call this Mashiro Moritaka here?
If they are a team, then I want to test the team's determination, not just Akito's.
Did it not work out after all?
Team up with me for a karate match against Miyoshi's dad!
He wants to test our determination as a team!
But I have nothing to do with this!
Apparently, Miyoshi's dad and Kawaguchi Tarou were old friends!
Once that came to light, it seemed like things were looking up,
but then he said he wanted to test our determination.
Sorry to call you here while you were working.
I saw you briefly at the funeral.
Well, let us get to the dojo.
That karate match thing was just an excuse to get you two away.
Some things are difficult to say in front of my wife and daughter.
Nobu was my best friend... and my rival in love.
How do you know about her?
Some letters from her were left in my uncle's office.
We got a general idea from those.
Hey, Nobu, why did you bring me out here?
You going to confess your love to me, or something?
I will say this only to you.
I do not swing that way
I just got a letter from Haruno.
But this is not a love letter.
It just says, Let us do our best in high school.
A girl as shy as her sending you a letter is pretty much the confession of a lifetime!
but I will be fine, since it is you.
Then can I write a reply?
I know the rest from reading the letters.
In the end, they never told each other their feelings, and Miyuki married someone else.
If he had just told her back then, who knows how things could have turned out?
Miyuki's daughter went to our middle school,
and she is dating Mashiro right now!
And this girl... well, her name's Azuki Miho.
I hear Kaya talking about her sometimes, but I did not...
Her dream's been to become a voice actress ever since middle school.
If he gets a fracture, he will not be able to write manga anymore.
You do not need to worry.
The karate thing was just an excuse.
Succeed as a manga artist, then get married, huh?
You have done enough, have not you?!
Why will not you tell her your feelings?!
I was just a bit lucky with my current serialization!
Until I succeed as a manga author and can make a living...
Do you have to do all this just to tell her how you feel?
Because I want to marry her!
If I date her, then it will be with the intention of marriage.
I cannot believe the nephew would take after his uncle so much.
I cannot help but cheer you on, too.
After seeing Nobu, I think it is best to be with the person you love as soon as possible.
If people make an honest effort, it will work out.
You seem like an honest guy.
Make your dream come true for Nobu's sake as well!
I will work hard for it!
I am so glad her parents were nice people.
I enjoyed learning more about my uncle.
Instead of replying to me, she calls you?
I will do my best so that you and Saiko can get married soon too!
Make sure to always get along with Kaya and Mashiro!
I am really happy for you two!
Let us make Tanto a big hit!
Because your lifestyle depends on it!
Sorry, but I am still getting things ready.
There is no way you would miss the New Year's party, Hiramaru.
Oh, congrats on your new serializaton!
I am Ibaraki, editor-in-chief of Jack SQ.
By the way, if there are any other stories you would like to write, by all means
Do you have any questions or concerns?
If you do, I will quickly
Oh, the seventh chapter was good, too?
I am so excited to read what happens next!
Hattori, I want to read the seventh chapter right away.
I am looking forward to it!
I do not know much about it, but there is some pretty good hype for Natural.
But do not you think they are being kind of cold?
You have shown some real talent by taking Akina Aiko's manuscript this far!
You thought of having Niizuma draw another manga.
Yes, I am happy to have a popular author in Jack draw it for me.
Indeed, Hattori is the rising star of the editorial department.
Niizuma, will you really be okay with five assistants?
I will be Jack' s number one author this year, too!
It seems like the editorial department's expecting a lot more from Natural than Tanto!
I definitely do not want to lose to Iwase.
This time we will overtake Eiji!
Arai, what are you doing after this?
There are things we cannot talk about while the editors are around.
Then let us go somewhere else.
What are you talking about with Aoki?
Let us all go to the afterparty!
But Ashirogi and Master Niizuma are still underage.
Then we can just go to a family restaurant!
Niizuma, let us go to a
I need to get back to work, so I am going home.
I am going to make a storyboard for the seventh chapter.
You have already done up through the third chapter,
so there is no need to rush.
I am having fun drawing manga right now!
I could barely pull myself away from drawing to come here today!
Okay, I will go grab it from the editorial department.
Then how about the rest of us go
Hiramaru, what are you doing there all alone?
Why are you backing them so much?
Niizuma, it is not good practice to support authors one is not in charge of.
If it looked like that to you, please do not tell anyone else.
That is why I am bringing it up now.
In the future, Ashirogi will become one of the pillars of Jack.
I think so too, and I want it to happen soon.
So no matter how you support them, I will help you!
I will not lose to them!
Orihara got honorable mention for the Tezuka Prize.
I have got Takahama too, so you guys should be all set.
And I am his wife, Takagi Kaya!
They registered at the end of last year.
You are a freshman in college with a serialization and a wife?!
There really are a ton of strange manga authors!
I will do my best too!
The two of us will live here from now on.
Your dad's giving us the realtor hookup, huh?
No, I will make us happy.
I brought the publishing sample of +NATURAL.
And CROW's got one in the middle?
It is already a Niiuzma Eiji issue.
Well, he is drawing both of them.
They do not want people to overlook either of them.
Anyway, let us check out Natural.
It is got an indie vibe.
But even though all the conventions of a first chapter are being broken, it still feels mainstream!
It is not about defeating some enemy
and wrapping things up in one chapter,
but you can definitely tell it is a shounen manga.
He is following the pattern of stuff like Pokemon by hatching the egg into various monsters.
As for franchise opportunities, if it were turned into a card game, kids would probably love it.
Otters 11 will be turned into a late-night anime!
Not even I could lie about that.
I am so glad I followed you!
I have been a terrible person for thinking of you
as a long-haired narcissistic con man who tricked me time and time again!
So that is what you think of me?
Well, not that you are wrong.
We will announce it in the magazine this spring.
The anime starts in the fall.
You understand, do not you, Hiramaru?
No, for the rest of the year, I will not breathe a word about taking a break!
I cannot tell him that no matter how long we wait, we will never get an offer for an evening timeslot.
Well, you know, it has a pretty dark theme.
This should be good for a while.
Otters and CROW got an anime.
Fukuda and Aoki's look promising, so if we do not pull out all the stops, we will be left behind.
The first chapter of Tanto has already been sent to the press.
The storyboards up to chapter three have been finalized.
The rest is out of our hands.
Oh, have you come up with an idea for the invention that will appear in the fourth chapter?
I was going to wait for the results of the first chapter and revise it based on that.
Still, you need to be brainstorming ideas one after another.
I will make a list by tomorrow.
This week's Jack is completely sold out in every convenience store and bookstore!
It is only 3 PM on a Monday!
Is it the Niizuma Eiji effect?!
It has to be a coincidence!
Everyone was buzzing about it on the Internet yesterday before it went on sale.
They were saying that +NATURAL is going to be great!
All copies were sold out yesterday.
It is first place in the preliminary polls!
And now for the final results...
It is first place by a long shot!
All that is changed since it ranked third last week is Natural being placed at the top.
Natural is first place, after all?
I really do not want Tanto's first chapter to rank under Natural's second chapter.
I know how you feel, but plot-driven manga and gag manga are different.
Anything in the top three is a great success.
We stopped by the convenience store, but...
No, by tonight, they will all be gone!
I told you before that getting fifth place with a gag manga is a good thing!
It will definitely be a big hit with the kids!
You will feel a lot better if you move around some!
How do you know where we live?
I really just wanted to congratulate you.
Until a little while ago, you were saying you were in love with my man!
But I cannot take her congratulations seriously!
I liked the Takagi with talent.
What the hell does that mean?!
You have more talent than me!
That is what you wanted to hear, right, Iwase?
Ever since middle school, Takagi Akito has only had eyes for me.
I do not need your congratulations.
You should hurry up and find some other guy with more talent than him.
You are just blowing hot air.
But he is a man with great talent that I can admire.
He is the man I like.
Your sixth chapter came in 11th, as well.
The first chapter was 5th, the second was 9th,
and ever since then, it is stayed at 11th place.
In a sense, it is stable.
Hey, guys, you should feel proud.
The lead editor even said it is been a long time since Jack had a manga that is well-received by the younger readers.
Kids usually pick their top three manga based on how funny they think it is, not the quality of the plot.
Gag manga have the advantage there.
I do not care about that!
We have to think about how we can do better!
How to pull in more kids?
Will Tanto become a boom, or will Tanto start a boom?
Starting a boom with a gag manga...
Some signature joke that will stick in kids' heads...
It may be a bit old, but something like Iyami's Shii!
If you repeat the same joke over and over, it can become a meme!
If I have something repeatable, it might make writing jokes easier.
We can get better rankings if we change how we do things!
The seventh chapter's still at 2nd place...
Well, it is not as if CROW dropped in popularity.
Speaking of rankings, your favorite Ashirogi has settled at 11th place.
The editorial department is saying things like, Looks like Ashirogi can do gag manga too,
and Manga that bring in younger readers are valuable.
What do you think of Tanto?
I am not reading it anymore!
Is it okay for us to continue Tanto like this?
Do not say something so unnerving right before my wedding ceremony!
In order to achieve your dream,
you need to stick to your goals!

News New work by Niizuma Eiji a hot topic before it even goes on sale!
Entertainment: In next week's Shounen Jack, on sale the 18th, +Natural will begin serialization.
This is a new work by popular author Niizuma Eiji of CROW fame.
The manuscript is done by amateur novel contest winner Akina Aiko.
Niizuma Eiji's CROW is also currently in serialization, which means he will have an unprecedented two simultaneous serializations in Jack.
From the moment it was announced in the magazine, it is been a hot topic on the Internet, and is causing waves.
